</div>
		<div class="entry clear">
        
          
                <p><b>Weird Tales</b> (<a href="https://mporcius.blogspot.com/2025/08/weird-tales-may-1941-counselman-jacobi.html">M Porcius</a>): The May 1941 issue of <i>Weird Tales</i> is like a<img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-103402" src="http://www.castaliahouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/weird_tales_194105-179x256.jpg" alt="" width="179" height="256" srcset="http://www.castaliahouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/weird_tales_194105-179x256.jpg 179w, http://www.castaliahouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/weird_tales_194105-160x229.jpg 160w, http://www.castaliahouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/weird_tales_194105.jpg 224w" sizes="(max-width: 179px) 100vw, 179px" /> monument to the genius of Hannes Bok, with a Bok cover and an interior chockablock with Bok illustrations of horrible monsters and alluring ladies.  So this issue of D. McIlwraith&#8217;s magazine is already getting the MPorcius Seal of Approval even before I read any of the fiction.</p>
<p><b><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-103403" src="http://www.castaliahouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Goodman-256x122.jpg" alt="" width="256" height="122" srcset="http://www.castaliahouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Goodman-256x122.jpg 256w, http://www.castaliahouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Goodman-160x76.jpg 160w, http://www.castaliahouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Goodman-768x365.jpg 768w, http://www.castaliahouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Goodman.jpg 1024w, http://www.castaliahouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Goodman-538x256.jpg 538w" sizes="(max-width: 256px) 100vw, 256px" />Appendix N </b>(<a href="https://goodman-games.com/adventures-in-fiction-lord-dunsany-3/">Goodman Games</a>): Some Appendix N authors directly influenced the creation of fantasy role-playing. We see concrete inspiration in the trolls borrowed from Poul Anderson or the “Vancian” magic system of <strong>D&amp;D</strong>. Other Appendix N writers exerted a less obvious influence, providing more a sense of tone and wonder than any specific element.</p>
<p><b>Star Trek</b> (<a href="https://comicsradio.blogspot.com/2025/08/haldemans-star-trek-novels-part-1.html">Comics Radio</a>): <i>Planet of Judgment</i> is the first of two Trek novels<img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-103404" src="http://www.castaliahouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Comics-Radio-151x256.jpg" alt="" width="151" height="256" srcset="http://www.castaliahouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Comics-Radio-151x256.jpg 151w, http://www.castaliahouse.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Comics-Radio.jpg 236w" sizes="(max-width: 151px) 100vw, 151px" /> written by noted SF author Joe Haldeman, back when Bantam Books had the franchise license and their occasional novels were the only new stories we poor Trekkies could get.  <a href="http://www.castaliahouse.com/sensor-sweep-lord-dunsany-red-sonja-movie-michael-moorcock/#more-103401" class="more-link">Read More</a></p>
  
         

